Key Match Events: Evan Mobley scored 34 points and 10 rebounds, leading the Cavaliers to a 134-122 victory over the Mavericks.
Cleveland scored 20 unanswered points in the second quarter to extend their lead.
Donovan Mitchell and Darius Garland contributed with 15 and 16 points respectively, along with key three-pointers.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Mavericks were playing without Kyrie Irving (illness) and Luka Doncic (calf), impacting their performance.
Cleveland shot 53.1 percent from the field and 37.5 percent from three-point range.
